			<span class="by"><span class="byby">by </span><a href="//slashdot.org/~King_TJ">King_TJ</a>  <span class="uid"><a href="//slashdot.org/~King_TJ">( 85913 )</a></span></a></span><span class="writes" style="display:none"> writes:</span> 
			<span class="otherdetails" id="comment_otherdetails_64457081"></span>
		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64457081"><p>There's a weird/disturbing trend in the media in the last few years where we're told what "people are angry/offended/upset by", and yet every time? It seems like nobody reading these articles encountered the claimed issue UNTIL they read about it. It winds up where everyone's discussing the non-issue, simply because they were all told by the news stories it was a thing.</p><p>Remember the hidden evil and perversion behind the Starbucks logo?</p><p><span class="substr"> </span> <a href="https://doctordavidfriedman.com/blog/the-hidden-evil-and-perversion-behind-starbucks-logo" title="doctordavidfriedman.com">https://doctordavidfriedman.co...</a> [doctordavidfriedman.com] </p></div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_64457081">

